  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 6dcf5dedf477f544b95e72d414f7b792, type: 3}
  m_Name: Ocean Spirits
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  encounterName: Ocean Spirits
  text: 'As your ship crests a wave and smoothly glides down, a movement to your
    left catches your eye. Four animal heads shaped of water emerge next to your
    ship: a horse, a fish, a shark, and a crab. Their watery mouths move as if to
    speak to you, but nothing comes out. Half a second later, you feel their words
    pierce your brain, speaking directly to your mind. "What offerings do you bring
    us?"'
  opt1Text: Offer up gold
  opt1Cost: 0a000000
  opt1Gain: 00000000030000000000000003000000
  opt1GainHidden: 1
  opt1Outcome: The spirits jump and dash in the rolling waters around the boat in
    a hypnotic dance, and as they crescendo, the jump into the water and dissapear.
    A few moments later, as the trance wears off, you notice a pile of fish and crab,
    still flopping around on the deck.
  opt2Text: Offer up food
  opt2Cost: 0000000004000000
  opt2Gain: 
  opt2GainHidden: 1
  opt2Outcome: It is difficult to read their liquid expressions, but they seem to
    accept this offering. Each head bows to you before dipping back under the waves.
  opt3Text: Shoot them
  opt3Cost: 00000000000000000100000003000000
  opt3Gain: 
  opt3GainHidden: 1
  opt3Outcome: Nobody demands anything from you! You bark the orders to man the cannons
    and in an instant, the crew comes alive. The spirits have barely any time to
    react before you give the order to fire. Your ears ring and black smoke fills
    the air as every cannon on the side of the ship goes off into the four spirits.
    During the barrage, you make out that one of spirits got hit, but another flexed
    their oceanly muscles and ripped one of your crew off your ship. As the black
    smoke settles, they are gone, as is your crewmate.
  opt4Text: Offer nothing
  opt4Cost: 00000000000000000000000001000000
  opt4Gain: 
  opt4GainHidden: 1
  opt4Outcome: You laugh at their request, and order the men to sail on. As you look
    back at the spirits, their expressions are angry, and you get a bad feeling about
    your decision.
